& [SOPHypergraphRecord] is social_periphery_interest_fabric_091
  + [record_type] is periphery_realization
  + [focus_subject] is Social Periphery Interest Fabric
  + [inside] is crawler pattern lineage, local interest digest, shared interest space, local social network, periphery signature, synchronized perspective, recommendation candidate, trust lens, explanation gate, and implementation boundary
  + [boundary] is user-owned digests, consented sharing, compatible trust scopes, visible recommendation explanation, Security/Honesty review, local identity boundary, privacy gates, and no runtime crawler
  + [outside] is silent browsing crawl, social graph scraping, private message capture, credentials, hidden identity, raw private data, global truth, centralized compulsory ranking, and implementation before gates

  = realization: the Google-like pattern generalizes from crawling public documents to mapping consented interest/periphery packets across social networks
  = caution: the same pattern becomes surveillance if raw browsing, private social data, or unconsented social graph edges become scan surfaces
  = wisdom: shared periphery can surface recommendations and association routes when overlap is explainable, trust-lensed, and kept distinct from truth or endorsement
  = implementation_status: future blocked specification, with first safe prototype limited to local synthetic packet comparison

